race.comment: GO FLASH GO (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 6 lengths at this track in a handy 27.60 beating Miss Maisie. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Expected to go well again. MISTER MANFREDI (3) produced a moderate performance last time when fifth at Bendigo over 500m behind Key Philosophy (28.47) in a Grade 5 H. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings seven times from 11 starts. One of the main contenders. DASH OF WHISKY (2) was in the minor money with a useful 24.05, finishing third in a Special conditions H at Bendigo last start. This tougher but looks a leading chance again. DOONGALLA DON (7) will give backers a sight.
